Juventus winger, Douglas Costa, has snubbed forward, Cristiano Ronaldo, in naming the club’s best player. According to Costa, forward, Paulo Dybala is the best player at Juventus ahead of Ronaldo. The 29-year-old noted that Ronaldo is only the second-best behind Dybala. When asked about the best player at the club in an Instagram Q&A, the Brazilian said: “The strongest companion is Paulino Dybala. “Then, of course, also Ronaldo.” Ronaldo is Juventus’ top scorer so far this season with 21 goals in Serie A. The Portugal captain had scored more goals than Dybala this campaign before the season was suspended due to the Coronavirus pandemic.